<subSubSection pageId="491" pageNumber="492" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="491" pageNumber="492">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="491" pageNumber="492">
This species ranges from Maryland (Erwin 1981b: 160) to southeastern Minnesota (Allen 1972: 137), including north-central Ohio (Lee 1994: 61) and southern Ontario (Lindroth 1966: 539), south to southeastern Louisiana and southern Georgia (Torres and Ruberson 2006: 32) [see Allen 1972: Fig. 158]. The record from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Connecticut”">&quot;Connecticut&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Bousquet and Larochelle 1993:) was based on a misidentified specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="491" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitiosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="491" pageNumber="492">Loxandrus vitiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Krinsky and Oliver 2001: 102).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
